edit_description: Replace the leafy tree canopy with bare, leafless branches.
critic_notes: The leafy canopy on the large left-side tree was replaced with bare branches in a physically plausible way. However, the edit is not minimal: additional trees/shrubs in the left background also appear to have reduced foliage/turned barer compared to the original. To improve, confine the change strictly to the specified tree canopy and keep all other vegetation unchanged.

edit_description: Add a large dark soot stain and streaking across the building facade.
critic_notes: The requested soot stain/streaking on the building facade is not convincingly added. Instead, there appears to be a broad blurry dark smudge/band across the lower-right area (including storefront/shutter zone) that looks like an editing artifact rather than physically plausible soot streaks. It also affects a wider area than a localized facade stain. Repair: add textured, irregular soot discoloration anchored to facade features (e.g., below windows/vents), with directional vertical streaking and proper blending to the wall surface, keeping the change confined strictly to the facade.

edit_description: Replace the leafy green canopy with bare, leafless branches by desaturating and removing the foliage texture on the tree canopy.
critic_notes: The canopy was successfully changed from leafy green to mostly bare branches and looks plausible. However, the edit is not minimal: it affects many trees across the scene (overall vegetation/seasonal look) rather than being localized to just the specified tree canopy, and the surrounding foliage/greenery appearance shifts noticeably. To improve, restrict the mask to only the target canopy area and avoid altering other trees/understory or global color/season cues.

edit_description: Repaint the tree trunk with dark, blotchy staining to make it look diseased and neglected.
critic_notes: The edited image appears essentially unchanged: the tree trunk does not show added dark, blotchy staining consistent with disease/neglect. No obvious drift in scene, camera, or lighting, but the requested trunk repainting is not evident. Reapply a localized texture/paint edit on the visible trunk area (left foreground) with darker irregular blotches while preserving existing bark texture and scene lighting.

edit_description: Repaint the school bus with dull, faded, patchy paint and visible rust streaks.
critic_notes: The requested edit was not applied to the school bus. In the edited image, the yellow school bus at right appears to have been replaced/changed into a white vehicle, which is a major content change rather than repainting. To fix: keep the same bus and only modify its paint surface—reduce saturation/brightness, add patchy faded areas and localized rust streaks—without changing the vehicle type, position, or the rest of the scene.
